lead_paragraph: Kyle Lowry had 26 points and 10 assists, DeMar DeRozan also scored 26 points and the Toronto Raptors set a franchise record with their 10th consecutive victory, 103-93 over the New York Knicks on Thursday night.

headline.print_headline: Lowry, DeRozan Each Have 26, Raptors Win 10th Straight
